span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 29, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104dzq1665703131639.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/dzq1665703131639.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/dzq1665703131639.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"dzq1665703131639\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"dzq1665703131639__udetailpos_401472\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Return the coordinates of a double-click.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"dzq1665703131639__topic_d118979e1_d118980e1_d118981e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dzq1665703131639__p_d118982e1_d118983e1_d118984e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">short udetailpos (POINT*</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">point</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">);</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"dzq1665703131639__topic_d84822e1_d84823e1_d84824e1_d84825e1_d84826e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1026165e67\">Parameters </h2>\n<dl class=\"dl parml\" id=\"dzq1665703131639__parml_kj3_gcs_zvb\">\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">point</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">A structure of type <code class=\"ph codeph\">POINT</code>, (defined in\n                     <code class=\"ph codeph\">windows.h</code>). The members x and y of this structure contain the\n                  coordinates of the double-click. (Output)</dd>\n</dl>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"dzq1665703131639__topic_d84827e1_d84828e1_d84829e1_d84830e1_d84831e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1026165e92\">Return Values</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"dzq1665703131639__table_d14804e1_d14805e1_d14806e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Values returned by udetailpos</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"dzq1665703131639__table_d14804e1_d14805e1_d14806e1__entry__1\">Value</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"dzq1665703131639__table_d14804e1_d14805e1_d14806e1__entry__2\">Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dzq1665703131639__table_d14804e1_d14805e1_d14806e1__entry__1\">0</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dzq1665703131639__table_d14804e1_d14805e1_d14806e1__entry__2\">The call was successful.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dzq1665703131639__table_d14804e1_d14805e1_d14806e1__entry__1\">-1</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dzq1665703131639__table_d14804e1_d14805e1_d14806e1__entry__2\">The call failed. This occurs if you did not get\n                        here via a double-click.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"dzq1665703131639__topic_d84832e1_d84833e1_d84834e1_d84835e1_d84836e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1026165e144\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dzq1665703131639__d6421e20\">Microsoft Windows platforms only. In library\n          <span class=\"ph filepath\">yrtl</span>. </p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"dzq1665703131639__topic_d84837e1_d84838e1_d84839e1_d84840e1_d84841e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1026165e157\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dzq1665703131639__p_d119003e1_d119004e1_d119005e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">udetailpos</code> returns the x and y coordinates of the last double-click on a graphic image displayed in Uniface. The x and y coordinates are expressed in pixels, relative to the upper left-hand corner of the image. If the image is smaller than the field it is displayed in, it is possible to receive values that are outside the boundaries of the image.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dzq1665703131639__p_d119006e1_d119007e1_d119008e1\">The coordinates are valid only if this function is called during processing of the detail trigger of an image field. In all other cases they will be invalid, and the function will return –1.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">In a Uniface form, define a field of type Image, and display an image in\n            it. In the detail trigger of that field, call a 3GL function, for example\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">perform \"DOCLICK\"</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">This 3GL function then calls <code class=\"ph codeph\">udetailpos</code> to process the\n            mouse click further, for example:</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104dzq1665703131639_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"dzq1665703131639__codeblock_zyx_3cs_zvb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">#include &lt;h3gl.h&gt;\n#include &lt;windows.h&gt;\nEXPORT void DOCLICK()\n{\nPOINT p;\n\nudetailpos(&amp;p);\nu_printf(\"You clicked on x=%d, y=%d\\n\", p.x, p.y);\n/* Further actions dependent on x and y values */\n}</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527048\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527048\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "udetailpos Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 29, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Return the coordinates of a double-click. short udetailpos (POINT* point ); Parameters point A structure of type POINT , (defined in windows.h ). The members x and y of this structure contain the coordinates of the double-click. (Output) Return Values Table 1. Values returned by udetailpos Value Description 0 The call was successful. -1 The call failed. This occurs if you did not get here via a double-click. Use Microsoft Windows platforms only. In library yrtl . Description udetailpos returns the x and y coordinates of the last double-click on a graphic image displayed in Uniface. The x and y coordinates are expressed in pixels, relative to the upper left-hand corner of the image. If the image is smaller than the field it is displayed in, it is possible to receive values that are outside the boundaries of the image. The coordinates are valid only if this function is called during processing of the detail trigger of an image field. In all other cases they will be invalid, and the function will return –1. In a Uniface form, define a field of type Image, and display an image in it. In the detail trigger of that field, call a 3GL function, for example perform \"DOCLICK\" . This 3GL function then calls udetailpos to process the mouse click further, for example: Explain this code #include <h3gl.h> #include <windows.h> EXPORT void DOCLICK() { POINT p; udetailpos(&p); u_printf(\"You clicked on x=%d, y=%d\\n\", p.x, p.y); /* Further actions dependent on x and y values */ } Copy Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}